The paper discusses algorithms for tensor decomposition, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. The evaluation of the algorithms involves measuring time, space, and fit, which are important considerations in the field of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
